# part 7: Yum Repo
1- Install tmux on your machine
2- Install apache server on your machine(httpd) and Install mysql.
3- Create a local yum repository on your local machine(available publicly) with the zabbix rpms:
https://repo.zabbix.com/zabbix/4.4/rhel/7/x86_64/
4- Disable all other repositories and keep only the new repo
5- Install zabbix rpms from the new repo (Download zabbix, zabbix-web,php, zabbix-server,
zabbix-agent rpm’s and their dependencies)

dnf install tmux -y # Install tmux (terminal multiplexer)
dnf install httpd -y # Install Apache HTTP server (used to publish the local repo)
dnf install mariadb-server -y # Install MariaDB (MySQL-compatible database for Zabbix)
systemctl enable --now httpd # Enable and start Apache
systemctl enable --now mariadb # Enable and start MariaDB
mkdir -p /var/www/html/zabbix # Directory where RPMs will be stored and served via HTTP
cd /var/www/html/zabbix
curl -O https://repo.zabbix.com/zabbix/7.0/rhel/9/x86_64/zabbix-server-mysql-7.0.21-release1.el9.x86_64.rpm # Download Zabbix server RPM
curl -O https://repo.zabbix.com/zabbix/7.0/rhel/9/x86_64/zabbix-web-7.0.21-release1.el9.noarch.rpm # Download Zabbix web frontend RPM
curl -O https://repo.zabbix.com/zabbix/7.0/rhel/9/x86_64/zabbix-agent-7.0.21-release2.el9.x86_64.rpm # Download Zabbix agent RPM
dnf install epel-release -y # Enable EPEL repository (needed for extra dependencies like fping)
dnf --enablerepo=BaseOS --enablerepo=AppStream --enablerepo=epel download \
php-bcmath php-common php-fpm php-gd php-ldap php-mbstring php-mysqlnd php-xml \
OpenIPMI-libs unixODBC fping # Download all Zabbix dependencies locally (PHP, DB, monitoring libs)
createrepo /var/www/html/zabbix # Create repository metadata so DNF can use this directory as a repo
[local-zabbix]
name=Local Zabbix Repository
baseurl=http://localhost/zabbix/
enabled=1
gpgcheck=0 
dnf config-manager --disable \* # Disable all other repositories
dnf config-manager --enable local-zabbix # Enable only the local Zabbix repository
dnf install zabbix-server-mysql zabbix-web zabbix-agent -y # Install Zabbix packages ONLY from the local repository


notes:
tmux is a terminal multiplexer: run multiple terminal sessions in one window. Can detach and reattach sessions. Useful for long-running tasks like installing packages or building a repo.
httpd (Apache) → Used to publish the local YUM repository over HTTP so DNF can access it..
MariaDB → Required backend database for Zabbix server.
RPM = Red Hat Package Manager (or .rpm file) It’s a package format used in Red Hat–based Linux systems.
-O → save the file with the same name as on the server.
Local YUM repo: Created to install packages without internet access, using locally downloaded RPMs.
EPEL repo: Some dependencies (like fping) are not available in BaseOS/AppStream, so EPEL is required.

